Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Let butter soften, then mix all ingredients together except raspberry jam. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mixture. Press pastry mixture into 8-inch square pan then place raspberry jam over it making sure there is 1/2 inch border on all sides. Sprinkle reserved mixture of top. Bake for 40-50 minutes or until light brown. Let cool on wire rack before cutting into bars.